Graham Toal (gtoal@an-teallach.com) wrote:

--- snip ---

: I'm still not exactly sure what the difference between Algotronix's
: EPLDs, and Xylinx's FPGAs is, but they definitely push them as being
: something vastly superior to Xylinx's FPGAs...

--- snip ---

I think the Altera EPLDs are significantly faster than the Xylinx
parts.  The Altera stuff is programmed like an EPROM (high voltage,
erase w/UV light) (at least they all used to be) whereas the Xylinx
parts are RAM based - new programs can be loaded on the fly from
a serial port.

